Credits / provenance

The Pac-Man hardware RTL is MikeJ's fpgaarcade VHDL model, integrated via the
MiSTer Arcade-Pacman core (maintained by Alexey "Sorgelig" Melnikov and the
MiSTer-devel project); the Z80 is Daniel Wallner's T80. All carry 3-clause BSD
headers, retained intact in src/fpga/core/rtl/. The MiSTer /sys framework (GPL)
is NOT included — this repository ships only the BSD core RTL plus an original
Analogue Pocket APF wrapper.

This core contains NO game ROMs. Pac-Man and Ms. Pac-Man are trademarks of
Bandai Namco Entertainment Inc.; this is an independent, hardware-compatible
FPGA implementation, not affiliated with or endorsed by Bandai Namco.
